fields.question: What does the wine tasting tour from Lisbon include?
fields.answer: Our wine tasting tours were created by local experts with precise attention to details to provide the best experience. The visitors don’t have to worry about the details, as each experience includes pick up and drop off from Lisbon, a guided tour to the vineyards, wineries and surroundings, wine tasting, and opportunities to learn about the original winemaking process.

fields.question: Are there private wine tasting tours available?
fields.answer: Yes, we provide two options for our visitors: group and private tours. All the tours are carefully created to guarantee positive impressions, but private ones can be customized for special occasions to give a more extensive experience. Contact us for more information and to make arrangements.

fields.question: Are the wine tasting tours suitable for the whole family?
fields.answer: As wine tours include wine tasting, they are created for adults. But children and people who don’t drink alcohol are also welcomed as the tours are not only wine tasting but also educational, so can be interesting for all categories of tourists. The detailed program of all available tours is given below. Contact us for more information.

fields.question: What is the duration of wine tasting tours from Lisbon?
fields.answer: In order to enjoy the wine tasting tour from Lisbon, be ready to spend between 4 to 6 hours. The total time depends on the specific itinerary, the road conditions, and the distance to the vineyards. Private tours can be adjusted up to your request. You can find more details in the description of the selected experience or by contacting us.

fields.question: What types of wines are included in the wine tasting experience?
fields.answer: Our wine tasting tours are created to provide an opportunity to savour the best tastes of Portugal. The variety of available wines is huge. It includes regional reds, whites, and rosés samples. We’ve created our experiences on the base of traditional and innovative winemaking styles from local wineries in the Lisbon region to satisfy the requests of all categories of visitors.

fields.question: What time of the year is suitable for a wine tasting tour from Lisbon?
fields.answer: Our wine tasting tours are available all year round. The wineries are open regardless of the season, but if you want to see the winemaking process, the best time to visit is from September to October, when there is a harvest season. But even in the winter season, we guarantee an overall positive experience for this type of tour as the weather in Portugal is mild and pleasant.

fields.question: What is included in private tours from Lisbon?
fields.answer: All private experiences including picking up from the hotel or any other desired location, transfer to the sightseeing, and bringing it back. This is included in the price and tourists don’t need to pay extra for these services. Tipping is always left to the discretion of the clients.

fields.question: How far in advance should I book a private tour in Lisbon?
fields.answer: It's always an individual decision. Some tours are already booked a month in advance and some are available even 5 days in advance. If you want to get on the tour and not worry that it will not be available, it is better to book the tour in advance.

fields.question: Can I book a private tour for a corporate event or special occasion?
fields.answer: Yes, when you book a private tour you are the main person and all the attention is on you. Accordingly, you can order a tour for yourself, your family, your company, or a special event. The main thing is to warn the tour company in advance, discuss all the details with it and tell them about your preferences.

fields.question: What are the must-see attractions to visit in Lisbon for private tours?
fields.answer: If you are planning a private tour of Portugal's capital, you must visit Lisbon's symbol, the Belem Tower. The Jeronimos Monastery, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, will amaze you with its architecture. Lisbon Cathedral, the oldest cathedral in the city, will take you back to the XII century, and St. George's Castle, located on a hill, will give you stunning views of the city and the river.

fields.question: How many days should I stay in Lisbon to fully enjoy private tours?
fields.answer: Lisbon can take weeks to see, but if you want to see the most popular sights, museums and churches, you need at least 3 days. During this time, you can enjoy the city's outstanding sites without rushing, learn their history, and take lots of cool photos.

fields.question: Are private tours available in languages other than English?
fields.answer: In most cases, yes. However, if you are interested in a particular language, it is better to familiarize yourself with it on the official website of the tour company. The fact is that each private excursion has different conditions and may offer various available languages of tours.

fields.question: Can I bring my pet on a group tour?
fields.answer: This depends on the specific tour. Some allow pets if it has been agreed in advance and provisions have been made for their comfort. Other tours may have restrictions due to the route, location, or other group members. It is recommended to check all details with the tour organizer in advance.

fields.question: Do the local guides guide the group tours?
fields.answer: Yes, group tours are conducted exclusively by experienced local guides who often know more than one language. These guides usually have in-depth knowledge of the history, culture, and attractions of the region, which helps to provide participants with valuable insights and enrich their tour experience.

fields.question: What is the average duration of a group tour in Lisbon?
fields.answer: The average length of a group tour in Lisbon ranges from 4 to 10 hours, depending on the specific tour. Short excursions can cover the main sights in a few hours, while longer tours include visits to several sites, detailed guided walks, and optional activities with refreshments at local restaurants. It is best to check the program of a particular tour before booking.

fields.question: Can I request a specific language guide for a group tour?
fields.answer: Yes, you can request a guide who speaks a specific language for a group tour. Often the excursion is available in the most popular languages to meet the needs of the participants. It is best to make your inquiry in advance of booking to ensure that the guide is available in the language you need.

fields.question: What hidden gems should I see in Lisbon on a group tour?
fields.answer: Lisbon's hidden gems are worth visiting, such as the Alfama quarter with its narrow streets and atmospheric fado bars, the Miradoro de Santa Catarina observation deck, which offers stunning views of the city, and Edward VII Park, where you can enjoy the silence and beautiful scenery. These places will add to the uniqueness of your tour.

fields.question: What transportation is used for the group tours?
fields.answer: A bus is used during a group tour of Lisbon. This is a convenient and economical way of transportation that allows you to visit all the key attractions of the city. The bus is equipped with air conditioning and comfortable seats. You can relax and enjoy the views without worrying about parking and routes.

fields.question: What must be visited during a sightseeing tour of Lisbon?
fields.answer: During a tour of Lisbon, be sure to visit Belém Tower, which offers magnificent views, and Jerónimos Monastery, a Manuelino masterpiece. Commerce Square will charm you with its beautiful buildings and restaurants. Stroll through the Alfama district with its narrow streets and fado music. Enjoy panoramic views of the city from Edward VII Park. Lisbon will surprise you with its rich history and unique atmosphere.

fields.question: Which payment methods are accepted to book a sightseeing tour?
fields.answer: There are no restrictions on payment in Lisbon. All restaurants, museums, exhibitions, and shopping centers accept both bank cards and cash. However, in any case, it is better to take cash with you, as some souvenir shops may not accept debit or credit cards.

fields.question: How many days should I stay in Lisbon to fully enjoy sightseeing tours?
What are the best attractions to visit in Lisbon with kids on sightseeing tours?
fields.answer: In Lisbon, for children, it is worth visiting the Oceanarium, where you can see many sea creatures, the Park of Nations with its modern attractions and pavilions, as well as the Zoo, where there is a cable car and a variety of animals. These places will give children a vivid impression and make the excursion unforgettable.

fields.question: Can I disembark at any attraction along the route and rejoin later?
fields.answer: Yes, you can disembark at any attraction along the route and join the group later. The main thing is to notify the guide or tour organizer of your intention in advance. This will ensure your safety and allow the group to adjust the route to pick you up conveniently.

fields.question: Are sightseeing tours wheelchair accessible?
fields.answer: Yes, most sightseeing tours are equipped for wheelchair access. However, this depends on the specific tour and itinerary. It is better to check with the tour organizer in advance to make sure that the necessary facilities are available and to ensure comfortable participation in the tour.

fields.question: How far in advance should I book a wine tour in Lisbon?
fields.answer: For a private wine tour in Lisbon, it is recommended to book 2-3 weeks in advance, especially in high season. This ensures that tourists can choose the locations and the desired guide. However, some tours require booking a month before the trip. It may be rational to avoid disappointment as such tours are in demand among the willing.

fields.question: Are there any age restrictions for participants on wine tours?
fields.answer: Age restrictions rarely apply to private wine tours. However, some tours may be adult-oriented due to alcohol tasting, so if you are not of legal age, the tour may refuse to allow you to sample alcoholic beverages. Keep in mind that it is worth checking all the details with the tour organizers.

fields.question: What is included into the wine tours in Lisbon?
fields.answer: The cost of a private wine tour usually includes transportation. For example, the tour may offer a comfortable bus or minivan for easy travel between wineries. If transportation is an additional cost, it is worth clarifying this when booking. Several wine tours offer the opportunity to purchase wine beverages to take home if desired.

fields.question: Can I bring my pet for the wine tour with me?
fields.answer: The ability to bring your pet on a tour depends on the policies of the company and discussed individually. Many wine tours are prepared to meet your needs, but it is worth notifying them in advance to arrange special arrangements for your comfort.

fields.question: Are wine tours suitable for solo travelers, couples, or small groups?
fields.answer: Private winery tours are great for a variety of groups: solo travelers, couples, or small companies. They offer the opportunity to maximize your enjoyment of wine culture and create unforgettable memories for a lifetime, which can be especially appealing for romantic couples or small groups of friends.

fields.question: What is the cancellation policy for wine tours?
fields.answer: Private wine tour cancellation policies can vary greatly from tour operator to tour operator. Some companies offer flexible terms, allowing you to cancel for free a few days before the tour starts. While others may charge penalties for last minute cancellations. Therefore, before booking, it is important to carefully study and understand the cancellation terms and conditions to avoid misunderstandings and unforeseen expenses.

fields.question: Are Lisbon food tours available in languages other than English?
fields.answer: Lisbon Food Tours stands out for its multilingual approach, offering private tours in several languages such as Spanish, French and Italian in addition to English. This allows tourists from different countries to feel comfortable and welcomed as they can communicate in their native language, which enriches their travel experience. This approach contributes to a better understanding of Lisbon's culture and traditions, making the tour even more memorable and enriching.

fields.question: Can I choose the start time for my food tour?
fields.answer: The choice of private tour start time is usually provided for the convenience of the tourists. You are free to discuss your preferred time with the tour organizer, taking into account your schedule and plans for the day. This allows you to maximize your enjoyment of every moment of the tour while feeling comfortable and relaxed.

fields.question: Are there any hidden fees associated with Lisbon food tours?
fields.answer: The costusually includes basic expenses such as guide services, food and beverage tastings, and transportation costs, if applicable. However, there may be additional costs for certain services or products, such as additional tastings, personal shopping or entrance fees to museums or other attractions. It is therefore worth checking before booking whether all costs are included in the tour price or whether there are any additional charges.

fields.question: Can I request specific attractions or destinations to visit on my food tour?
fields.answer: It depends on the type of the tour. The itinerary of the group tour is fixed, When planning a private tour, you are free to express your preferences regarding the places you would like to visit. The tour organizers are ready to listen to your wishes and take them into account when drawing up the itinerary. This may include visits to specific restaurants, cafes, stores or even historical sites that interest you. Flexibility in planning allows us to create the most satisfying and memorable experience for you.

fields.question: How much flexibility is there in the itinerary of Lisbon food tour?
fields.answer: The itinerary is usually fixed unless it’s private one. You can discuss with the organizer various itinerary options, including visits to a variety of places, from traditional restaurants and cafes to local markets with unique products. This approach allows you to create a rich and memorable experience that fully meets your expectations.

fields.question: Can I combine different types of food tasting in Lisbon food tour?
fields.answer: Yes, it is possible to mix different types of experiences into one package if it’s a private one, but the itinerary of a group one is already fixed. This can include culinary outings with tastings of local food and drink, visits to historical sites and points of interest, and experiencing local culture through interaction with locals.

fields.question: Are there any special discounts for booking multiple food and wine tours?
fields.answer: Lisbon food and wine is an affordable service, attractive for different types of group travel or family events. Therefore, special discounts are often offered when booking multiple tours. This saves on the total cost and creates a more diverse experience for each participant, ensuring accessibility and meeting the needs of a diverse group.

fields.question: Are food and wine tours suitable for people with mobility issues?
fields.answer: Lisbon food and wine tours are willing to adapt itineraries for people with reduced mobility. The organizers are ready to discuss the individual needs of each participant and provide suitable options, such as more accessible places to visit or alternative means of transportation, so that everyone can enjoy the tour comfortably and without problems.

fields.question: Can I book a food and wine tour for a corporate event or special occasion?
fields.answer: You can book a food and wine tour for a corporate event or special occasion. The organizers are ready to provide personalized options including themed itineraries, wine and local food tastings, and special arrangements to make your event memorable and unique. They pay attention to every detail to create a unique experience that will delight you and your guests.

fields.question: How can I get feedback on special requests for my food and wine tour experience?
fields.answer: You can get feedback directly from us. We highly appreciate your opinion and strive to development. That's why you can contact us to express your impressions and suggestions to improve the service.

fields.question: Can I extend the duration of my food and wine tour while on the trip?
fields.answer: The group tour has a fixed itinerary. Extending the duration of a private tour during the trip is usually possible, but requires prior agreement with the tour operator. Additional charges for additional time and services may be required. It is therefore recommended to discuss this issue in advance.

fields.question: Are there any exclusive experiences available only on food and wine tours?
fields.answer: Yes, there are often exclusive experiences available only with Lisbon food and wine tours. These may include private tastings at renowned wineries or hidden gems, personalized cooking classes with local chefs, behind-the-scenes access to traditional food production methods, or intimate dining experiences at off-the-beaten-path restaurants. Such experience opens up unique opportunities that may not be available on group tours.

fields.question: How can I join a guided tour in Lisbon?
fields.answer: Joining a guided tour in Lisbon is easy and convenient. To participate in the tour, you can book online on the company's website, familiarize yourself with the schedule, and choose a convenient time. You can also contact the agency by phone and book a tour.

fields.question: Can I request a guided tour for my friends or family?
fields.answer: Yes, booking a guided group tour in Lisbon for your company or family is a great way to enjoy the city in a cozy setting and on your schedule. You can choose an itinerary that fits your interests and preferences, and determine a convenient time and date for your tour. This is a great option for those who want to see Lisbon in the company of close friends or relatives, enjoying a personalized approach and attention to detail from professional guides.

fields.question: What is the average duration of a guided tour in Lisbon?
fields.answer: The average duration of a guided tour in Lisbon can vary depending on the chosen itinerary and tour content. Typically, tours lasting between 2 and 4 hours allow you to cover the city's main attractions. However, the duration may vary depending on the specific interests of the group or the topic of the tour. Some tours may be more in-depth and last longer, especially if they cover a wider range of locations or include visits to museums, monuments, and other sites.

fields.question: Are there any discounts available for large groups?
fields.answer: Special discounts on group tours in Lisbon are often available for large groups. Before booking, it is worth contacting the agency to clarify the terms of cooperation and the possibility of getting a discount. Usually, discounts are available when booking for a group of a certain size, for example, 10 people or more. It's also worth checking if there are any additional bonuses or customized offers for your group.

fields.question: Are group tours guided by experienced local guides?
fields.answer: Yes, many group tours are led by knowledgeable locals or professional guides with an in-depth knowledge of Lisbon. This allows you to get a unique and authentic perspective on the city and learn many interesting and fascinating things about its history, culture, and traditions.

fields.question: Can I book a group tour last minute or is advanced booking required?
fields.answer: The ability to book a group tour at the last minute depends on the availability of space on a particular tour and company policy. Some tours may be available for last-minute booking, while others may require advance booking. To be sure, it is best to contact the tour operator directly and clarify this information.

fields.question: What are the most popular landmarks covered in your historical tours?
fields.answer: Popular attractions on historical Lisbon tours include the famous Belem Tower, the city's symbol Christos Monashes, and the ancient Alfama district with its narrow streets and many historical monuments. Also included in the itinerary are the famous Plaça Comercio and the main streets of the city center, revealing Lisbon's rich history.

fields.question: Are historical tours available in multiple languages?
fields.answer: Tours cover a wide range of languages including English, Spanish, French, German, and others. The tours strive to maximize the comfort of all our guests by providing a choice of the language that is most comfortable for them. This allows each tour participant to feel confident and understand the information conveyed on the tour. Regardless of the language you prefer, the guided tours ensure that your journey will be interesting, informative, and memorable.

fields.question: How long do historical tours typically last?
fields.answer: The average duration of our excursions is from 4 to 10 hours, depending on the chosen route and planned stops. The professional guides would make the program rich and interesting so that each participant gets maximum information and experience in the allotted time.

fields.question: Can I hop on and off the historical tour bus at different stops?
fields.answer: Some of the historical tours include stops so that participants can get off the bus and take a closer look at the sights and capture them in photographs. This provides a unique opportunity to not only see places in real-time but also to get a more in-depth experience of them. The professional guides are happy to share more information about each place, as well as suggest which moments are worth capturing in photos.

fields.question: Are there any historical walking tours in Lisbon?
fields.answer: Yes, some of the tours below include walking tours with a professional guide. This allows guests to get a more in-depth experience of the city's historic districts, visit places inaccessible by bus, and hear interesting stories and legends about Lisbon.

fields.question: Are tickets for historical  tours available online or only in person?
fields.answer: Tickets for the historical tour can be purchased either online on our website or in person on-site at our tourist information centers or offices. Online booking provides convenience and guarantees your place on the excursion, especially during periods of high demand.

fields.question: Are there any discounts for children or seniors on walking tours?
fields.answer: Many companies and travel agencies that conduct walking tours of Lisbon offer discounts for children and seniors. This may be a certain percentage of the tour price or special rates for certain age categories. It is recommended to clarify the availability and terms of discounts when booking a tour.

fields.question: What to bring on a walking tour in Lisbon?
fields.answer: For a walking tour, it's recommended to bring comfortable walking shoes, a hat, sunscreen protection, sunglasses, and a bottle of water. Depending on the weather conditions, it's also recommended to bring a light jacket or an umbrella. And of course, don't forget your camera for the memorable pictures!

fields.question: Are there any restrictions on photography during walking tours?
fields.answer: Photography is generally allowed during tours, but there may be restrictions on the use of flash in museums or other venues. Some tours may also prohibit photography and videography inside certain locations or under certain conditions. It is recommended that you check with your tour guide before starting your tour for photo regulations.

fields.question: Are walking tours wheelchair accessible?
fields.answer: This question should be discussed individually. Not all tours may be accessible to persons with disabilities due to the nature of the routes and attractions. It is recommended to contact the tour provider to clarify the possibility of organizing a tour for people with disabilities.

fields.question: What is the frequency of departures for walking tours?
fields.answer: The frequency of departure of walking tours can vary depending on the time of year, the popularity of the itinerary, and company policy. Tours are usually scheduled for a specific time and day of the week and information about this is available when booking. It is recommended to check the schedule and availability of the tour in advance.

fields.question: Do walking tours operate year-round or only during certain seasons?
fields.answer: Most companies offer Lisbon tours year-round, but some may have seasonal schedules depending on demand and weather conditions. In summer, there are often additional tours due to increased tourist traffic, while in winter there may be fewer offerings. It is recommended that you familiarize yourself with the tour schedule and possible changes depending on the season in advance.

fields.question: How flexible can a beach tour itinerary be?
fields.answer: The flexibility of a private tour itinerary with Lisbon beach tours can be very flexible, especially when booking a customized tour. When planning such a tour, you can influence the choice of beaches to visit, the length of stay at each beach, and the inclusion of additional activities or attractions in the itinerary. This allows you to customize the tour to suit your interests, preferences, and timetable, making your beach vacation as comfortable and satisfying as possible.

fields.question: Can I book Lisbon beach tours to get a more personalized experience?
fields.answer: Booking a private Lisbon beach tour represents an ideal option for those who prefer a personalized approach and a personalized experience. The trip is customized to your desires, allowing you to select the beaches you would like to visit and determine the length of stay at each. This also opens up the possibility of adding optional activities, such as visiting local attractions or dining at an ocean-view restaurant.

fields.question: How can I learn more about Lisbon's history and culture on Lisbon beach tours?
fields.answer: The guides accompanying Lisbon beach tours usually have an in-depth knowledge of Lisbon's history and culture and are happy to share this information with tour participants. During the tour, they talk about historical events, architecture, local culture, and traditions, making your trip more informative and entertaining.

fields.question: Can I leave any attraction on Lisbon beach tours and join it later?
fields.answer: Flexibility in schedule and itinerary is an important aspect that can be provided by some Lisbon beach tour operators. This means that participants can temporarily break away from the group to enjoy some moments on the beach or visit interesting places in the surrounding area, and then join the group later. However, not all tour operators offer this flexibility, so it is important to clarify this possibility in advance when booking a tour.

fields.question: Are there any special events or festivals included in Lisbon beach tours?
fields.answer: Planning to include special events or festivals in Lisbon beach tours depends on the tour operator and the time of year. Some tours may be specially planned so that participants can enjoy local events taking place on or near the beaches. These may include events such as holiday celebrations, music concerts, fairs, or cultural festivals. When booking a tour, it is advisable to check whether such events are included in the program and what their dates are, so that you can plan your trip in the best possible way.

fields.question: Are there any hidden fees associated with private beach tours?
fields.answer: Hidden fees associated with private Lisbon beach tours may arise in the form of additional charges for certain services or unexpected fees. However, to avoid such surprises, it is advisable to carefully review the booking conditions and the contract with the tour operator to be aware of all possible additional fees. It is important to clearly discuss all the details of the tour and clarify which services are included in the price and for which you will have to pay extra.

fields.question: What hidden gems should I see in Lisbon on a half-day tour?
fields.answer: On a half-day excursion in Lisbon, be sure to stop by Monstrum, a small park with stunning views of the city and the Tagus River. Then head to the Costa de Caparica, where you can enjoy the cozy atmosphere of the local beaches and cafes. Despite their modest size, these places offer a unique experience and allow you to experience the spirit of Lisbon in just a few hours.

fields.question: Which payment methods are accepted?
fields.answer: Lisbon accepts a variety of payment methods. Cash is accepted everywhere, as well as credit and debit cards such as Visa and Mastercard. Some places may have restrictions on using cards, so it's always better to play it safe and take cash. Many stores and restaurants also accept payments through mobile payment apps such as Apple Pay or Google Pay.

fields.question: How can I learn more about the history and culture of Lisbon during the half-day tour?
fields.answer: During a sightseeing tour of Lisbon, you can learn more about its history and culture by listening to the stories of the guides. They usually share interesting facts and explain the meanings of monuments and architectural landmarks. Don't forget to ask your guide questions - this is a great way to deepen your knowledge of the city. You can also get acquainted with the city using audio guides, information brochures, or mobile applications.

fields.question: How long do half-day tours typically last?
fields.answer: Half-day tours typically last between 4 and 7 hours, depending on the route and number of attractions you visit. This time period is usually sufficient to get acquainted with the main attractions of the city and get a general idea of its culture and history.

fields.question: Are there any half-day tours tailored to specific interests, such as food or history?
fields.answer: Yes, there are group half-day tours that focus on different interests such as food, history, art, and more. For example, culinary excursions may include visits to local markets, tastings of local dishes, and excursions to typical restaurants. Historical tours involve visits to historical monuments, museums, and archaeological sites.

fields.question: Can I book a half-day tour last minute or is advanced booking required?
fields.answer: It is often possible to book a half-day tour to Lisbon at the last minute depending on availability and demand. It may be possible to secure a spot on a tour a day in advance, but advance booking is recommended, especially during busy seasons or for tours with limited numbers of participants. This will secure your place and save you the stress of unexpected rejections.

fields.question: How many days should I stay in Lisbon to fully enjoy sunset tours?
fields.answer: To fully enjoy sunset tours of Lisbon, it is recommended to stay in the city for 1-2 days. This time is enough to get acquainted with the main attractions of the city and pay attention to the amazing sunsets. However, if you have more time, you can immerse yourself more deeply in Lisbon and explore its culture, cuisine, and history.

fields.question: How can I join a sunset tour in Lisbon?
fields.answer: To join a sunset tour in Lisbon, you have several options. The first option is to book a tour online on our website. You can also contact us beforehand in order to get information about available tour options and make reservations.

fields.question: Are there any sunset tour packages that include multiple attractions?
fields.answer: Almost all sunset tour packages in Lisbon include visits to several attractions. They usually cover various aspects of the city, including historical monuments, cultural sites, architectural landmarks, and panoramic views. The main part of such tours is evening picnics at sunset and a photo part.

fields.question: Are there any discounts available for large groups on sunset tours?
fields.answer: In such cases all the additional discounts are shown on the booking page or can be discussed additionally with the company. This policy ensures transparency and equality for all tourists, guaranteeing the same conditions and costs for members of the tour.

fields.question: Can I request a specific language guide for a sunset tour?
fields.answer: Yes, you can request a guide in a specific language for your sunset tour. Tour staff are professional and most are multilingual, so we can provide the right guide to make your excursion as comfortable and understandable as possible. The languages available are often Portuguese, English, French, and Spanish.

fields.question: What are the best attractions to visit in Lisbon with kids on sunset tours?
fields.answer: The best attractions to visit in Lisbon with kids on sunset tours include São Jorge Castle, which offers stunning views of the city and river, and the Aguas Livres Aqueduct, where you can stroll and admire the majestic architecture. In addition, parks and public gardens, such as the Parc des Nations and the Botanical Garden, offer wonderful places to relax and stroll.
